{"title_page": "Scottish Libertarian Party", "text_new": "{{short description|Political party in Scotland}}\n{{Infobox political party\n| colorcode = {{Scottish Libertarian Party/meta/color}}\n| leader = Tam Laird<ref name=scotlibs1>{{cite web | url=https://scottishlibertarians.com/key-members/ | title=Key Members | accessdate=29 March 2017 | work=Scottish Libertarians}}</ref>\n| foundation = 2012\n| ideology = {{Nowrap|[[Libertarianism]]<br>[[Classical liberalism]]<br>[[Night-watchman state|Minarchism]]<br>[[Individualism]]<br>[[Scottish independence]]<ref name=nutt1 /><br>[[Euroscepticism|Soft Euroscepticism]]}}\n| position = Fiscal: [[Right-wing politics|Right]] to [[Far-right politics|Far right]]<ref>http://scottishlibertarians.com/policies/</ref>                    \nSocial: [[Left-wing politics|Left]] to [[Far-left politics|Far-left]] <ref>http://scottishlibertarians.com/policies/</ref>\n| website = {{url|https://scottishlibertarians.com/}}\n| name = Scottish Libertarian Party\n| native_name = P\u00e0rtaidh Libeirt\u00e8ireach na h-Alba<br>Scots Libertarian Pairty\n| headquarters = 14-18 East Shaw Street<br>Kilmarnock<br>KA1 4AN<ref>http://search.electoralcommission.org.uk/English/Registrations/PP3906</ref>\n| party_articletitle = \n| logo = [[File:Scottish Libertarian Party logo 2016.png|250px|Scottish Libertarian Party Logo]]\n| leader1_title = Deputy Leader\n| leader1_name = Stef Johnstone<ref name=scotlibs1 />\n| colours = {{Color box|#F0DC82|border=darkgray}}{{Color box|#006CB4|border=darkgray}} [[Buff (colour)|Buff]] and [[Blue]]<ref>https://scottishlibertarians.com/where-we-are/</ref>\n| seats3_title = [[House of Commons of the United Kingdom|Scottish seats in the House of Commons]]\n| seats3 = {{Composition bar|0|59|hex={{Scottish Libertarian Party/meta/color}}}}\n| seats5_title = [[Scottish Parliament]]\n| seats5 = {{Composition bar|0|129|hex={{Scottish Libertarian Party/meta/color}}}}\n| seats6_title = [[Local government in Scotland]]\n| seats6 = {{Composition bar|0|1227|hex={{Scottish Libertarian Party/meta/color}}}}\n| international = [[International Alliance of Libertarian Parties]]\n}}\n\nThe '''Scottish Libertarian Party''' ({{lang-gd|P\u00e0rtaidh Libeirt\u00e8ireach na h-Alba}}, {{Lang-sco|Scots Libertarian Pairty}}) is a [[libertarianism|libertarian]], [[Euroscepticism|Eurosceptic]] [[List of political parties in Scotland|political party in Scotland]].\n\n== History ==\nThe party was first founded on 3 January 2012<ref>{{cite web | url=https://scottishlibertarians.com/scottish-libertarian-party-process/ | title=Formation Process For Scottish Libertarians Political Party | date=3 January 2012 | accessdate=4 May 2016 | work=Scottish Libertarians}}</ref> under the leadership of author Daniel Logan-Scott.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://scottishlibertarians.com/a-message-from-the-party-leader/ | title=A Message from the Party Leader | date=25 March 2012 | accessdate=4 May 2016 | author=Logan-Scott, Daniel | work=Scottish Libertarians}}</ref> The party was refused registration by the [[Electoral Commission (United Kingdom)|Electoral Commission]] due to naming similarities with the [[Libertarian Party (UK)|Libertarian Party UK]]. This was resolved when the Libertarian Party UK altered its registration to no longer stand candidates or run in [[elections in Scotland]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://scottishlibertarians.com/another-hurdle-passed/ | title=Another Hurdle Passed For Scottish Libertarian Party | date=22 May 2012 | accessdate=4 May 2016 | author=Logan-Scott, Daniel | work=Scottish Libertarians}}</ref> Despite organising various events, the party became inactive and stopped updating the blog.\n\nAfter 3 years of inactivity, the Scottish Libertarian Party launched again in December 2015 under new leader Alan Findlay,<ref name=nutt1>{{cite web | url=http://www.thenational.scot/politics/new-scottish-libertarian-party-set-to-launch-and-call-for-independence.10658 | title=New Scottish Libertarian Party set to launch and call for independence | date=1 December 2015 | accessdate=4 May 2016 | author=Nutt, Kathleen | work=The National}}</ref> officially registering with the Electoral Commission in March 2016.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://search.electoralcommission.org.uk/English/Registrations/PP3906 | title=Registration summary | accessdate=4 May 2016 | work=The Electoral Commission}}</ref>\n\nIn the [[2016 Scottish Parliament election]] the party stood in the [[West Scotland (Scottish Parliament electoral region)|West Scotland]],<ref name=\"West region list\">{{cite web |url=http://www.renfrewshire.gov.uk/media/1927/List-of-candidates-West-Scotland-Region/pdf/RegionalCandidates.pdf |title=Scottish Parliamentary election \u2013 regional contest. West Scotland Region. Statement of persons and parties nominated and Notice of poll |publisher=[[Renfrewshire Council]] |date=1 April 2016 |accessdate=4 April 2016}}</ref> [[Mid Scotland and Fife (Scottish Parliament electoral region)|Mid Scotland and Fife]], [[North East Scotland (Scottish Parliament electoral region)|North East Scotland]]<ref name=\"NE candidates\">{{cite web |url=http://www.aberdeencity.gov.uk/CouncilNews/ci_cns/pr_SPnominatedpersons010416.asp |title=Close of nominations \u2013 candidates for Aberdeen seats |publisher=[[Aberdeen City Council]] |date=1 April 2016 |accessdate=4 April 2016}}</ref> regions and the [[Edinburgh Central (Scottish Parliament constituency)|Edinburgh Central]] constituency.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.edinburghnews.scotsman.com/news/politics/edinburgh-s-parliament-election-candidates-named-1-4088458 |title=Edinburgh\u2019s parliament election candidates named |work=Edinburgh Evening News |date=1 April 2016 |accessdate=2 April 2016}}</ref> The party received its highest percentage of votes in Edinburgh Central with 0.3%, or 119 votes. The party received 650 votes in Mid Scotland and Fife, 552 in North East Scotland and 480 in West Scotland, for a total of 1,805 votes in Scotland.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/politics/scotland-constituencies/S16000104/|title=Edinburgh Central - Scottish Parliament constituency - Election 2016|website=BBC News|access-date=2016-05-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/politics/scotland-regions/S17000013/|title=Mid Scotland and Fife - Scottish Parliament electoral region - Election 2016|website=BBC News|access-date=2016-05-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/politics/scotland-regions/S17000014/|title=North East Scotland - Scottish Parliament electoral region - Election 2016|website=BBC News|access-date=2016-05-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/politics/scotland-regions/S17000016/|title=West Scotland - Scottish Parliament electoral region - Election 2016|website=BBC News|access-date=2016-05-06}}</ref>\n\nIn the [[2019 United Kingdom general election|2019 general election]] the party fielded one candidate in the constituency [[Kilmarnock and Loudoun (UK Parliament constituency)|Kilmarnock and Loudoun]], getting 405 votes (0.9% of the votes cast).<ref name=\"GE2019 result\">{{cite web |url=https://www.scotsman.com/news/politics/scotland-general-election-results-2019-in-full-winners-in-all-59-constituencies-1-5061921 |title=Scotland General Election results 2019 in full: Winners in all 59 constituencies |publisher=[[The Scotsman]] |date=13 December 2019 |accessdate=18 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://scottishlibertarians.com/ Official website]\n* [https://app.box.com/s/3lubadnmg32qkgzlsij4s7spy4nf5uq7 2016 Manifesto]\n\n{{Nationalism in the United Kingdom}}\n{{Scottish parliamentary parties}}\n\n[[Category:Libertarian parties]]\n[[Category:Libertarian parties in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:2012 establishments in Scotland]]\n[[Category:Eurosceptic parties in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Political parties established in 2012]]\n[[Category:Political parties in Scotland]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Political party in Scotland}}\n{{Infobox political party\n| colorcode = {{Scottish Libertarian Party/meta/color}}\n| leader = Tam Laird<ref name=scotlibs1>{{cite web | url=https://scottishlibertarians.com/key-members/ | title=Key Members | accessdate=29 March 2017 | work=Scottish Libertarians}}</ref>\n| foundation = 2012\n| ideology = {{Nowrap|[[Libertarianism]]<br>[[Classical liberalism]]<br>[[Night-watchman state|Minarchism]]<br>[[Individualism]]<br>[[Scottish independence]]<ref name=nutt1 /><br>[[Euroscepticism|Soft Euroscepticism]]}}\n| position = Fiscal: [[Right-wing politics|Right]] <ref>http://scottishlibertarians.com/policies/</ref>                       \nSocial: [[Left-wing politics|Left]] to [[Far-left politics|Far-left]] <ref>http://scottishlibertarians.com/policies/</ref>\n| website = {{url|https://scottishlibertarians.com/}}\n| name = Scottish Libertarian Party\n| native_name = P\u00e0rtaidh Libeirt\u00e8ireach na h-Alba<br>Scots Libertarian Pairty\n| headquarters = 14-18 East Shaw Street<br>Kilmarnock<br>KA1 4AN<ref>http://search.electoralcommission.org.uk/English/Registrations/PP3906</ref>\n| party_articletitle = \n| logo = [[File:Scottish Libertarian Party logo 2016.png|250px|Scottish Libertarian Party Logo]]\n| leader1_title = Deputy Leader\n| leader1_name = Stef Johnstone<ref name=scotlibs1 />\n| colours = {{Color box|#F0DC82|border=darkgray}}{{Color box|#006CB4|border=darkgray}} [[Buff (colour)|Buff]] and [[Blue]]<ref>https://scottishlibertarians.com/where-we-are/</ref>\n| seats3_title = [[House of Commons of the United Kingdom|Scottish seats in the House of Commons]]\n| seats3 = {{Composition bar|0|59|hex={{Scottish Libertarian Party/meta/color}}}}\n| seats5_title = [[Scottish Parliament]]\n| seats5 = {{Composition bar|0|129|hex={{Scottish Libertarian Party/meta/color}}}}\n| seats6_title = [[Local government in Scotland]]\n| seats6 = {{Composition bar|0|1227|hex={{Scottish Libertarian Party/meta/color}}}}\n| international = [[International Alliance of Libertarian Parties]]\n}}\n\nThe '''Scottish Libertarian Party''' ({{lang-gd|P\u00e0rtaidh Libeirt\u00e8ireach na h-Alba}}, {{Lang-sco|Scots Libertarian Pairty}}) is a [[libertarianism|libertarian]], [[Euroscepticism|Eurosceptic]] [[List of political parties in Scotland|political party in Scotland]].\n\n== History ==\nThe party was first founded on 3 January 2012<ref>{{cite web | url=https://scottishlibertarians.com/scottish-libertarian-party-process/ | title=Formation Process For Scottish Libertarians Political Party | date=3 January 2012 | accessdate=4 May 2016 | work=Scottish Libertarians}}</ref> under the leadership of author Daniel Logan-Scott.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://scottishlibertarians.com/a-message-from-the-party-leader/ | title=A Message from the Party Leader | date=25 March 2012 | accessdate=4 May 2016 | author=Logan-Scott, Daniel | work=Scottish Libertarians}}</ref> The party was refused registration by the [[Electoral Commission (United Kingdom)|Electoral Commission]] due to naming similarities with the [[Libertarian Party (UK)|Libertarian Party UK]]. This was resolved when the Libertarian Party UK altered its registration to no longer stand candidates or run in [[elections in Scotland]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://scottishlibertarians.com/another-hurdle-passed/ | title=Another Hurdle Passed For Scottish Libertarian Party | date=22 May 2012 | accessdate=4 May 2016 | author=Logan-Scott, Daniel | work=Scottish Libertarians}}</ref> Despite organising various events, the party became inactive and stopped updating the blog.\n\nAfter 3 years of inactivity, the Scottish Libertarian Party launched again in December 2015 under new leader Alan Findlay,<ref name=nutt1>{{cite web | url=http://www.thenational.scot/politics/new-scottish-libertarian-party-set-to-launch-and-call-for-independence.10658 | title=New Scottish Libertarian Party set to launch and call for independence | date=1 December 2015 | accessdate=4 May 2016 | author=Nutt, Kathleen | work=The National}}</ref> officially registering with the Electoral Commission in March 2016.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://search.electoralcommission.org.uk/English/Registrations/PP3906 | title=Registration summary | accessdate=4 May 2016 | work=The Electoral Commission}}</ref>\n\nIn the [[2016 Scottish Parliament election]] the party stood in the [[West Scotland (Scottish Parliament electoral region)|West Scotland]],<ref name=\"West region list\">{{cite web |url=http://www.renfrewshire.gov.uk/media/1927/List-of-candidates-West-Scotland-Region/pdf/RegionalCandidates.pdf |title=Scottish Parliamentary election \u2013 regional contest. West Scotland Region. Statement of persons and parties nominated and Notice of poll |publisher=[[Renfrewshire Council]] |date=1 April 2016 |accessdate=4 April 2016}}</ref> [[Mid Scotland and Fife (Scottish Parliament electoral region)|Mid Scotland and Fife]], [[North East Scotland (Scottish Parliament electoral region)|North East Scotland]]<ref name=\"NE candidates\">{{cite web |url=http://www.aberdeencity.gov.uk/CouncilNews/ci_cns/pr_SPnominatedpersons010416.asp |title=Close of nominations \u2013 candidates for Aberdeen seats |publisher=[[Aberdeen City Council]] |date=1 April 2016 |accessdate=4 April 2016}}</ref> regions and the [[Edinburgh Central (Scottish Parliament constituency)|Edinburgh Central]] constituency.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.edinburghnews.scotsman.com/news/politics/edinburgh-s-parliament-election-candidates-named-1-4088458 |title=Edinburgh\u2019s parliament election candidates named |work=Edinburgh Evening News |date=1 April 2016 |accessdate=2 April 2016}}</ref> The party received its highest percentage of votes in Edinburgh Central with 0.3%, or 119 votes. The party received 650 votes in Mid Scotland and Fife, 552 in North East Scotland and 480 in West Scotland, for a total of 1,805 votes in Scotland.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/politics/scotland-constituencies/S16000104/|title=Edinburgh Central - Scottish Parliament constituency - Election 2016|website=BBC News|access-date=2016-05-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/politics/scotland-regions/S17000013/|title=Mid Scotland and Fife - Scottish Parliament electoral region - Election 2016|website=BBC News|access-date=2016-05-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/politics/scotland-regions/S17000014/|title=North East Scotland - Scottish Parliament electoral region - Election 2016|website=BBC News|access-date=2016-05-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/politics/scotland-regions/S17000016/|title=West Scotland - Scottish Parliament electoral region - Election 2016|website=BBC News|access-date=2016-05-06}}</ref>\n\nIn the [[2019 United Kingdom general election|2019 general election]] the party fielded one candidate in the constituency [[Kilmarnock and Loudoun (UK Parliament constituency)|Kilmarnock and Loudoun]], getting 405 votes (0.9% of the votes cast).<ref name=\"GE2019 result\">{{cite web |url=https://www.scotsman.com/news/politics/scotland-general-election-results-2019-in-full-winners-in-all-59-constituencies-1-5061921 |title=Scotland General Election results 2019 in full: Winners in all 59 constituencies |publisher=[[The Scotsman]] |date=13 December 2019 |accessdate=18 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://scottishlibertarians.com/ Official website]\n* [https://app.box.com/s/3lubadnmg32qkgzlsij4s7spy4nf5uq7 2016 Manifesto]\n\n{{Nationalism in the United Kingdom}}\n{{Scottish parliamentary parties}}\n\n[[Category:Libertarian parties]]\n[[Category:Libertarian parties in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:2012 establishments in Scotland]]\n[[Category:Eurosceptic parties in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Political parties established in 2012]]\n[[Category:Political parties in Scotland]]\n", "name_user": "Dylan109", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.